featured_reviews.review_id: I think one of the best places I have ever visited. Well maintained historical architectural place. The history was written there in a board. I found it while riding bike and boy! I am glad that I found it. And am glad this hidden treasure is still hidden.
featured_reviews.review_text: I think one of the best places I have ever visited. Well maintained historical architectural place. The history was written there in a board. I found it while riding bike and boy! I am glad that I found it. And am glad this hidden treasure is still hidden.

featured_reviews.review_id: A historical site. A very unique structure as it is built in terracotta style (typical bengal) of architecture. Typically only temples were used to be built in this structure in ancient Bengal. A good and peaceful place to visit. There is no offerings in the current days as only the ruins are remaining but there are three catacombs of the persons involved from the family who built the mosque. I was on the way to somewhere else where I saw the ASI board and stepped into the site.

It is a unique brick built mosque decorated with terracotta ornamentation. It represents the terracotta elements of the Islamic architecture of Bengal.There are three tombs in the mosque complex. At present the ruined mosque is under the maintenance of the Archaeological Survey of India.

If you're planning for a day trip of Hooghly, you should add this place in your list!

featured_reviews.review_id: Here it's a terracotta mosque which is near about 500 years old and was built by Sayed Jamaluddin in the era of Nasiruddin Nasrat Shah .The heritage is situated at Adisaptagram beside the Saraswati river. It is an unique brick built mosque decorated with terracotta ornamentation. The mosque has three decorated mihrabs and corner minarets. The three tombs, on the south-eastern side are said to be associated with Sayed Fakhruddin(Father of Jamaluddin), his wife and his eunach. Presently this half ruined heritage is maintained by the Archaeological Survey of India.
